g.aria-label: Hey! I’ve just returned from Prof. Mukhi’s office and look what I’ve got with me! This is a physics question from last year’s Mimamsa used in the mains. They had uploaded it on their website it seems. It seems pretty interestinG. he gave me a day to solve it. Wanna solve together?
Sure! I’ve always heard seniors saying how Mimamsa’s questions are a test of our fundamental knowledge in the subjects and don’t need much calculations or rote memory.Let’s see if that’s true!
Ughh physics..Umm... I’m not really good at physics and even flopped my boards in physics. Plus idk I’ve lost touch with physics for a while so I dont think I’m cut out for this.

No worries man, I’m pretty sure questions are framed in such a way that people interested in a particular subject can attempt questions in other subjects as well, and in fact many of them are interdisciplinary too I’ve heard. Don’t worry, anyways we’re solving it together, right?
